<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC approved the spot Bitcoin ETFs a littl=
e after the close yesterday (Wednesday) afternoon. A little after the close=
 on=C2=A0<em>Tuesday=C2=A0</em>afternoon, the SEC=E2=80=99s account on X (f=
ormerly Twitter) tweeted that it had approved spot Bitcoin ETFs. That turne=
d out to be fake; the SEC=E2=80=99s Twitter got hacked. The SEC had to walk=
 back that statement on Tuesday, and then walk it forward again on Wednesda=
y. We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33970375.257=
410/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTA=
vdGhlLXNlYy1nb3QtdHJvbGxlZC1vbi1iaXRjb2luLWV0ZnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDExMTI0X01PTk=
VZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09M=
jQwMTExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB55d7d1d0" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">  talked about this yesterday</a>. =E2=80=9CNyah nyah nyah nyah nya=
h,=E2=80=9D I wrote.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When the Bitcoin ETFs got fake-approved on Tue=
sday, the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33970375=
.257410/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDE=
tMTAvdGhlLXNlYy1nb3QtdHJvbGxlZC1vbi1iaXRjb2luLWV0ZnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDExMTI0X0=
1PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlc=
m09MjQwMTExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC55d7d1=
d0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  price of Bitcoin</a> =E2=80=9Cposted a relatively modest jum=
p to almost $48,000 from about $46,700 before falling back toward $45,000=
=E2=80=9D when it turned out to be fake. I was a little perplexed =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0everyone expected the ETFs to be approved by today, so the fake tweet=
 didn=E2=80=99t add much fake information, and the retraction didn=E2=80=99=
t add much real information =E2=80=94=C2=A0but=C2=A0whatever. The fun fact =
is that, when Bitcoin ETFs got approved for real on Wednesday, the price of=
